This looks great, in the sense that it looks like standard boilerplate which you've faithfully implemented following another file :-) Modulo my pernickety comment about the name of a field nobody will ever say anyway, this looks great to me.

Thanks a lot! 

maintainer merge

My first reaction to this was "this shouldn't be called `isSomething` because it's not a Prop", but I now see that this is also the style used in `AlgebraCat`. That doesn't mean I like it though :-/ I started a Zulip discussion [here](https://leanprover.zulipchat.com/#narrow/stream/287929-mathlib4/topic/AlgebraCat.2EisRing.20isn't.20a.20Prop/near/443330331) and if we converge on e.g. `instBialgebra` then maybe you should make that change.
Thanks! `instBialgebra` sounds better to me, have changed it

You now deviate from `QuadraticModuleCat.lean`, defining `toIso` rather than `ofIso` in a different namespace, but to be honest I'm more confused about the naming convention in `QuadraticModuleCat` than what's going on here...

Yeah, with this I decided to be more like `AlgEquiv.toAlgebraIso`, `MulEquiv.toMonCatIso` and friends. I guess maybe it should be `BialgEquiv.toBialgebraCatIso`. There's also `BialgEquiv.toHopfAlgebraCatIso` in a later PR I think.

edit: it seems `FooEquiv.toFooCatIso` is the most common spelling so I've switched to that.
